modules.name: AWS.Inspector
modules.comments:
Amazon Inspector

Amazon Inspector enables you to analyze the behavior of your AWS resources and to identify potential security issues. For more information, see Amazon Inspector User Guide.

declarations.comments: Assigns attributes (key and value pairs) to the findings that are specified by the ARNs of the findings.
declarations.title: addAttributesToFindings

declarations.comments: Creates a new assessment target using the ARN of the resource group that is generated by CreateResourceGroup. If the service-linked role isn’t already registered, also creates and registers a service-linked role to grant Amazon Inspector access to AWS Services needed to perform security assessments. You can create up to 50 assessment targets per AWS account. You can run up to 500 concurrent agents per AWS account. For more information, see Amazon Inspector Assessment Targets.
declarations.title: createAssessmentTarget

declarations.comments: Creates an assessment template for the assessment target that is specified by the ARN of the assessment target. If the service-linked role isn’t already registered, also creates and registers a service-linked role to grant Amazon Inspector access to AWS Services needed to perform security assessments.
declarations.title: createAssessmentTemplate

declarations.comments: Creates a resource group using the specified set of tags (key and value pairs) that are used to select the EC2 instances to be included in an Amazon Inspector assessment target. The created resource group is then used to create an Amazon Inspector assessment target. For more information, see CreateAssessmentTarget.
declarations.title: createResourceGroup

declarations.comments: Deletes the assessment run that is specified by the ARN of the assessment run.
declarations.title: deleteAssessmentRun

declarations.comments: Deletes the assessment target that is specified by the ARN of the assessment target.
declarations.title: deleteAssessmentTarget

declarations.comments: Deletes the assessment template that is specified by the ARN of the assessment template.
declarations.title: deleteAssessmentTemplate

declarations.comments: Describes the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.
declarations.title: describeAssessmentRuns

declarations.comments: Describes the assessment targets that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment targets.
declarations.title: describeAssessmentTargets

declarations.comments: Describes the assessment templates that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment templates.
declarations.title: describeAssessmentTemplates

declarations.comments: Describes the IAM role that enables Amazon Inspector to access your AWS account.
declarations.title: describeCrossAccountAccessRole

declarations.comments: Describes the findings that are specified by the ARNs of the findings.
declarations.title: describeFindings

declarations.comments: Describes the resource groups that are specified by the ARNs of the resource groups.
declarations.title: describeResourceGroups

declarations.comments: Describes the rules packages that are specified by the ARNs of the rules packages.
declarations.title: describeRulesPackages

declarations.comments: Produces an assessment report that includes detailed and comprehensive results of a specified assessment run.
declarations.title: getAssessmentReport

declarations.comments: Information about the data that is collected for the specified assessment run.
declarations.title: getTelemetryMetadata

declarations.comments: Lists the agents of the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.
declarations.title: listAssessmentRunAgents

declarations.comments: Lists the assessment runs that correspond to the assessment templates that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment templates.
declarations.title: listAssessmentRuns

declarations.comments: Lists the ARNs of the assessment targets within this AWS account. For more information about assessment targets, see Amazon Inspector Assessment Targets.
declarations.title: listAssessmentTargets

declarations.comments: Lists the assessment templates that correspond to the assessment targets that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment targets.
declarations.title: listAssessmentTemplates

declarations.comments: Lists all the event subscriptions for the assessment template that is specified by the ARN of the assessment template. For more information, see SubscribeToEvent and UnsubscribeFromEvent.
declarations.title: listEventSubscriptions

declarations.comments: Lists findings that are generated by the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.
declarations.title: listFindings

declarations.comments: Lists all available Amazon Inspector rules packages.
declarations.title: listRulesPackages

declarations.comments: Lists all tags associated with an assessment template.
declarations.title: listTagsForResource

declarations.comments: Previews the agents installed on the EC2 instances that are part of the specified assessment target.
declarations.title: previewAgents

declarations.comments: Registers the IAM role that grants Amazon Inspector access to AWS Services needed to perform security assessments.
declarations.title: registerCrossAccountAccessRole

declarations.comments: Removes entire attributes (key and value pairs) from the findings that are specified by the ARNs of the findings where an attribute with the specified key exists.
declarations.title: removeAttributesFromFindings

declarations.comments: Sets tags (key and value pairs) to the assessment template that is specified by the ARN of the assessment template.
declarations.title: setTagsForResource

declarations.comments: Starts the assessment run specified by the ARN of the assessment template. For this API to function properly, you must not exceed the limit of running up to 500 concurrent agents per AWS account.
declarations.title: startAssessmentRun

declarations.comments: Stops the assessment run that is specified by the ARN of the assessment run.
declarations.title: stopAssessmentRun

declarations.comments: Enables the process of sending Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS) notifications about a specified event to a specified SNS topic.
declarations.title: subscribeToEvent

declarations.comments: Disables the process of sending Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS) notifications about a specified event to a specified SNS topic.
declarations.title: unsubscribeFromEvent

declarations.comments: Updates the assessment target that is specified by the ARN of the assessment target.
declarations.title: updateAssessmentTarget

declarations.comments: You do not have required permissions to access the requested resource.
declarations.title: AccessDeniedException

declarations.comments: Used in the exception error that is thrown if you start an assessment run for an assessment target that includes an EC2 instance that is already participating in another started assessment run.
declarations.title: AgentAlreadyRunningAssessment

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector agent. This data type is used as a request parameter in the ListAssessmentRunAgents action.
declarations.title: AgentFilter

declarations.comments: Used as a response element in the PreviewAgents action.
declarations.title: AgentPreview

declarations.comments: You started an assessment run, but one of the instances is already participating in another assessment run.
declarations.title: AgentsAlreadyRunningAssessmentException

declarations.comments:
A snapshot of an Amazon Inspector assessment run that contains the findings of the assessment run .

Used as the response element in the DescribeAssessmentRuns action.
declarations.title: AssessmentRun

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector agent. This data type is used as a response element in the ListAssessmentRunAgents action.
declarations.title: AssessmentRunAgent

declarations.comments: Used as the request parameter in the ListAssessmentRuns action.
declarations.title: AssessmentRunFilter

declarations.comments: You cannot perform a specified action if an assessment run is currently in progress.
declarations.title: AssessmentRunInProgressException

declarations.comments: Used as one of the elements of the AssessmentRun data type.
declarations.title: AssessmentRunNotification

declarations.comments: Used as one of the elements of the AssessmentRun data type.
declarations.title: AssessmentRunStateChange

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector application. This data type is used as the response element in the DescribeAssessmentTargets action.
declarations.title: AssessmentTarget

declarations.comments: Used as the request parameter in the ListAssessmentTargets action.
declarations.title: AssessmentTargetFilter

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector assessment template. This data type is used as the response element in the DescribeAssessmentTemplates action.
declarations.title: AssessmentTemplate

declarations.comments: Used as the request parameter in the ListAssessmentTemplates action.
declarations.title: AssessmentTemplateFilter

declarations.comments: A collection of attributes of the host from which the finding is generated.
declarations.title: AssetAttributes

declarations.comments: This data type is used as a request parameter in the AddAttributesToFindings and CreateAssessmentTemplate actions.
declarations.title: Attribute

declarations.comments: This data type is used in the AssessmentTemplateFilter data type.
declarations.title: DurationRange

declarations.comments: This data type is used in the Subscription data type.
declarations.title: EventSubscription

declarations.comments: Includes details about the failed items.
declarations.title: FailedItemDetails

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector finding. This data type is used as the response element in the DescribeFindings action.
declarations.title: Finding

declarations.comments: This data type is used as a request parameter in the ListFindings action.
declarations.title: FindingFilter

declarations.comments: This data type is used in the Finding data type.
declarations.title: InspectorServiceAttributes

declarations.comments: Internal server error.
declarations.title: InternalException

declarations.comments: Amazon Inspector cannot assume the cross-account role that it needs to list your EC2 instances during the assessment run.
declarations.title: InvalidCrossAccountRoleException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because an invalid or out-of-range value was supplied for an input parameter.
declarations.title: InvalidInputException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it attempted to create resources beyond the current AWS account limits. The error code describes the limit exceeded.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it referenced an entity that does not exist. The error code describes the entity.
declarations.title: NoSuchEntityException

declarations.comments: Contains information about a resource group. The resource group defines a set of tags that, when queried, identify the AWS resources that make up the assessment target. This data type is used as the response element in the DescribeResourceGroups action.
declarations.title: ResourceGroup

declarations.comments: This data type is used as one of the elements of the ResourceGroup data type.
declarations.title: ResourceGroupTag

declarations.comments: Contains information about an Amazon Inspector rules package. This data type is used as the response element in the DescribeRulesPackages action.
declarations.title: RulesPackage

declarations.comments: This data type is used as a response element in the ListEventSubscriptions action.
declarations.title: Subscription

declarations.comments: A key and value pair. This data type is used as a request parameter in the SetTagsForResource action and a response element in the ListTagsForResource action.
declarations.title: Tag

declarations.comments: The metadata about the Amazon Inspector application data metrics collected by the agent. This data type is used as the response element in the GetTelemetryMetadata action.
declarations.title: TelemetryMetadata

declarations.comments: This data type is used in the AssessmentRunFilter data type.
declarations.title: TimestampRange

declarations.comments: Used by the GetAssessmentReport API. The request was rejected because you tried to generate a report for an assessment run that existed before reporting was supported in Amazon Inspector. You can only generate reports for assessment runs that took place or will take place after generating reports in Amazon Inspector became available.
declarations.title: UnsupportedFeatureException
